rComments: He is the best professor I've ever had in UofT. You'd never be bored in his lectures and tutorials. Quizzes are easy (as long as you review lecture stuff regularly) and tests are not hard. Great experience! I definitely would like to take advanced Japanese with him again!
amazing lectures and easy final test.
This professor is good and I really recommended him. But his quizes are too hard for us to finish it. Sometimes are easy but most of them are tough.
JOJO is about the best Japanese lecture you might have at UofT, very funny guy and easy-going about students who treat the class seriously, loves to be surprised.

Beloved by students who take Japanese, and for good reason. Lectures and lecture slides are clear and concise. Textbook is great but his lectures are even better. If you put in the time (weekly review), you will definitely learn a lot. Arimori-sensei is a funny, easygoing guy who knows his stuff and is passionate about teaching. Simply fantastic.
Very good professor and he is very cute in the way he speaks and explain things. One of the best prof in UofT. He did even better than my high school teacher :)

Hes the best prof at st. george campus and quite cute actually. but his quizzes are SUPER HARD and I mean it. I have some Japanese background and thot I would do really well in the course but his quizzes are just way too hard.

Amazing lecturer, nice personality. Extremely hard working prof. There are quizs every week,  and  they weigh quite lot.  The vocabulary ones are much easier than the grammar ones. Assignments and in class writing are basically free marks. Exams are not hard. Put in time and you will be rewarded
